Company Overview of Stellex Capital Management LP



Snapshot People




Company Overview
Stellex Capital Management LP is a private equity firm specializing in corporate buyouts, distressed and special situation corporate assets, Greenfield distressed investments, and secondary market transactions including the purchase of revolving credit and letters of credit facilities, bank loans, second lien debt, high yield bonds, and restructured equities. The firm typically invests in middle-market companies. It seeks to invest in service, manufacturing, and industrial companies, which includes aerospace, automotive, metal fabrication, business services, consumer products, defense, financial services, government services, telecommunications, media, and transportation, infrastructure, bui...
Stellex Capital Management LP is a private equity firm specializing in corporate buyouts, distressed and special situation corporate assets, Greenfield distressed investments, and secondary market transactions including the purchase of revolving credit and letters of credit facilities, bank loans, second lien debt, high yield bonds, and restructured equities. The firm typically invests in middle-market companies. It seeks to invest in service, manufacturing, and industrial companies, which includes aerospace, automotive, metal fabrication, business services, consumer products, defense, financial services, government services, telecommunications, media, and transportation, infrastructure, building products, and energy and power. The firm primarily invests in the United States and Europe. The firm seeks to make equity investment between $25 million and $100 million in companies with a maximum revenue of $2000 million. The firm purchases existing debt and equity instruments and also issues new debt and equity capital. It executes larger investments through partnering and co-investment with limited partners. Stellex Capital Management LP is based in New York, United States with an additional office in London, United Kingdom.
Detailed Description


